#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:8
msgid "Customizable Campaign Buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:10
msgid ""
"With :game:`Ares` you can have up to four campaign buttons on "
":game:`Yuri's Revenge`'s campaign selection menu and customize all of "
"them in :file:`uimd.ini`."
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:19
msgid ""
"You can customize all campaign buttons using these :file:`uimd.ini` tags "
"by replacing :tag:`X` by the numbers from :tag:`1` to :tag:`4`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:24
msgid ":tagdef:`[UISettings]CampaignX=battle`"
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:23
msgid ""
"The mission from :file:`battle.ini` started by clicking the image button."
" To hide a button set :tag:`CampaignX=no`. Defaults to :value:`ALL1`, "
":value:`SOV1`, :value:`TUT1` or :value:`no` respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:28
msgid ""
":tagdef:`[UISettings]CampaignX.Image=filename, *including* the .shp "
"extension`"
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:27
msgid ""
"The 260x136 image shown on the campaign selection menu. Have a look at "
":file:`fsalg.shp` to see an example. Defaults to :value:`fsalg.shp` or "
":value:`fsslg.shp` respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:31
msgid ""
":tagdef:`[UISettings]CampaignX.Palette=filename, *including* the .pal "
"extension`"
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:31
msgid ""
"The palette used to render the image. Defaults to :value:`fsalg.pal`, "
":value:`fsslg.pal` or :value:`fsbclg.pal` respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:36
msgid ":tagdef:`[UISettings]CampaignX.Subline=CSF label`"
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:34
msgid ""
"The subline displayed beneath the campaign image. To override the default"
" value set this to a label containing no text. Defaults to "
":value:`STT:AlliedCampaignIcon`, :value:`STT:SovietCampaignIcon` or "
":value:`STT:CampaignAnimTutorial` respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:41
msgid ":tagdef:`[UISettings]CampaignX.Tooltip=CSF label`"
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:39
msgid ""
"The text displayed as tooltip when the player hovers over the image. To "
"override the default value set this to a label containing no text. "
"Defaults to :tag:`CampaignX.Subline`."
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:43
msgid ""
":game:`Ares` defaults to the original game's values so you don't have to "
"change anything. To display a third button just add the above tags for "
":tag:`Campaign3`."
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:47
msgid ""
"Three buttons are arranged in a triangle formation: one centered in the "
"upper row, two in the lower one. If you want to have an upside-down "
"triangle, skip :tag:`Campaign3` and use :tag:`Campaign4` instead. Four "
"campaigns are always ordered left to right, top to bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:52
msgid ""
"To control the sound that is played when the player hovers over the image"
" see :tag:`HoverSound=` on :doc:`/ui-features/campaignlist`."
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst
msgid "Quickstart"
msgstr ""

#: ../ui-features/customizablecampaignbuttons.rst:55
msgid ""
"If you want to have a third campaign button to start the tutorial "
"mission, set :tag:`[UISettings]Campaign3.Image=fsbclg.shp`. You will have"
" to rework that image, as there is no :game:`Yuri's Revenge` style "
"version of it."
msgstr ""

